The paper discusses a method for improving the generalization of conditional generative models, which is a common topic in machine learning and artificial intelligence research (cs.LG, cs.AI). The method is applied to high-dimensional image and tabular data, which suggests a focus on computer vision and data analysis (cs.CV, cs.SI). The paper also mentions improving predictions for cellular perturbation response to treatment and disease based on high-dimensional single-cell gene expression data, which suggests a focus on bioinformatics and computational biology (cs.NE).
